	   <tr><td colspan=2>depends on the different settings..<br>times when you SHOULD have a pet...<br>1) When soloing<br>2) when your group either doesnt have any tanks for is low on tanks<br>3) Whne your group has a cleric and a druid already, so you are using your mana and doing SOMETHING for the group hehe<br>Times when NOT to summon a wolf pal....<br>1) in Dungeons, unless you are camping something by yourself or in a secluded area.<br>2) When you are the only healer (this is just my opinion)<br>3) If you are in a tank heavy group, or have lots of pet classes arleady in your group. <br>There are more examples im sure but i just cant think of any more. On saying that our pets arent that good... well thats a matter of an opinion. A raw pet where you didnt buff it or anything, is not worthless or weak, just not as strong as most pets. However, if you are playing as though a shm you will use your buffs, making your pet a kick butt lil dog. <br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
