	   <tr><td colspan=2>With regards to item #3 of when you SHOULD have a pet, it seems to me that Nitsujlak implied that if group has both druid and cleric already that shaman is next to worthless to group without his pet...&nbsp;&nbsp;Is that what was meant to be implied???  <br><br>It seems to me a shaman should ALSO be buffing his group with his mana if the group already has both a cleric and druid....  Also, shouldn't a shaman be debuffing and DOT'ing mobs?  Wolf is just a bonus in this situation.  It seems to me that a shaman would still be of benefit to the group in such a situation.  <br><br>I would be interested to hear from anyone with much more experience that I have regarding this...  Thanks.<br>&nbsp;<br>Kega, 30th lvl Wood Elf Druid of Povar<br>Kanu, 19th lvl Barbarian Shaman of Povar<br></td></tr>
